clockbase.Description: Returns the internal clock frequency of the device.

dios/0/drive.Description: When on (1), the corresponding 8-bit bus is in output mode. When off (0), it is in input mode. Bit 0 corresponds to the least significant byte. For example, the value 1 drives the least significant byte, the value 8 drives the most significant byte.

dios/0/input.Description: Gives the value of the DIO input for those bytes where drive is disabled.

dios/0/interface.Description: Selects the interface standard to use on the 32-bit DIO interface. A value of 0 means that a 3.3 V CMOS interface is used. A value of 1 means that an LVDS compatible interface is used.

Options.0: "manual": Enables manual control of the DIO output bits.
Options.16: "qa_result": Sends discriminated readout results to the DIO.
Options.32: "chan0seq", "channel0_sequencer": Enables control of DIO values by the sequencer of channel 1.
Options.33: "chan1seq", "channel1_sequencer": Enables control of DIO values by the sequencer of channel 2.

dios/0/output.Description: Sets the value of the DIO output for those bytes where 'drive' is enabled.

qachannels/0/readout/result/mode.Description: Selects the averaging order of the result.

Options.0: "cyclic": Cyclic averaging: a sequence of multiple results is recorded first, then averaged with the next repetition of the same sequence.
Options.1: "sequential": Sequential averaging: each result is recorded and averaged first, before the next result is recorded and averaged.

qachannels/1/input/overrangecount.Description: Indicates the number of times the Signal Input was in an overrange condition within the last 200 ms. It is checked for an overrange condition every 10 ms.

qachannels/1/markers/1/source.Description: Selects the source for the marker output.

qachannels/1/mode.Description: Selects between Spectroscopy and Qubit Readout mode.

Options.0: "spectroscopy": In Spectroscopy mode, the Signal Output is connected to the Oscillator, with which also the measured signals are correlated.
Options.1: "readout": In Qubit Readout mode, the Signal Output is connected to the Readout Pulse Generator, and the measured signals are correlated with the Integration Weights before state discrimination.

qachannels/1/output/range.Description: Sets the maximal Range of the Signal Output power. The instrument selects the closest available Range with a resolution of 5 dBm.

qachannels/1/readout/result/enable.Description: Enables the acquisition of readout results.

qachannels/1/readout/result/errors.Description: Number of hold-off errors detected since last reset.

qachannels/1/readout/result/length.Description: Number of data points to record. One data point corresponds to a single averaged result value of the selected source.

qachannels/1/readout/result/mode.Description: Selects the averaging order of the result.

Options.0: "cyclic": Cyclic averaging: a sequence of multiple results is recorded first, then averaged with the next repetition of the same sequence.
Options.1: "sequential": Sequential averaging: each result is recorded and averaged first, before the next result is recorded and averaged.

qachannels/1/readout/result/overdio.Description: Number of DIO interface overflows during readout. This can happen if readouts are triggered faster than the maximum possible data-rate of the DIO interface.

qachannels/1/readout/result/source.Description: Selects the signal source of the Result Logger.

Options.1: "result_of_integration": Complex-valued integration results of the Weighted Integration in Qubit Readout mode.

qachannels/1/spectroscopy/delay.Description: Sets the delay of the integration in Spectroscopy mode with respect to the Trigger signal. The resolution is 2 ns.

qachannels/1/spectroscopy/envelope/delay.Description: Sets the delay of the envelope waveform in Spectroscopy mode with respect to the Trigger signal. The resolution is 2 ns.

qachannels/1/spectroscopy/envelope/enabl.Description: Enables the modulation of the oscillator signal with the complex envelope waveform.

qachannels/1/spectroscopy/envelope/lengt.Description: Length of the uploaded envelope waveform in number of complex samples.

qachannels/1/spectroscopy/envelope/wave.Description: Contains the envelope waveform as a vector of complex samples.

qachannels/1/spectroscopy/length.Description: Sets the integration length in Spectroscopy mode in number of samples. Up to 33.5 MSa (2^25 samples) can be recorded, which corresponds to 16.7 ms.

qachannels/1/spectroscopy/result/acquire.Description: Indicates the index of the acquisition that will be performed on the next trigger.

qachannels/1/spectroscopy/result/average.Description: Number of measurements that are averaged. Only powers of 2 are valid, other values are rounded down to the next power of 2. 1 means no averaging. The maximum setting is 32768.

qachannels/1/spectroscopy/result/enable.Description: Enables the acquisition of spectroscopy results.

qachannels/1/spectroscopy/result/errors.Description: Number of hold-off errors detected since last reset.

qachannels/1/spectroscopy/result/length.Description: Number of data points to record. One data point corresponds to a single averaged result value of the selected source.

qachannels/1/spectroscopy/result/mode.Description: Selects the averaging order of the result.

Options.0: "cyclic": Cyclic averaging: a sequence of multiple results is recorded first, then averaged with the next repetition of the same sequence.
Options.1: "sequential": Sequential averaging: each result is recorded and averaged first, before the next result is recorded and averaged.

qachannels/1/spectroscopy/trigger/channe.Description: Selects the source of the trigger for the integration and envelope in Spectroscopy mode.

qachannels/1/triggers/0/imp50.Description: Trigger Input impedance: When on, the Trigger Input impedance is 50 Ohm; when off, 1 kOhm.

qachannels/1/triggers/0/value.Description: Shows the value of the digital Trigger Input. The value is integrated over a period of 100 ms. Values are: 1: low; 2: high; 3: was low and high in the period.

qachannels/1/triggers/1/imp50.Description: Trigger Input impedance: When on, the Trigger Input impedance is 50 Ohm; when off, 1 kOhm.

qachannels/1/triggers/1/value.Description: Shows the value of the digital Trigger Input. The value is integrated over a period of 100 ms. Values are: 1: low; 2: high; 3: was low and high in the period.

scopes/0/averaging/count.Description: Configures the number of Scope measurements to average.

scopes/0/channels/0/enable.Description: Enables recording for this Scope channel.

scopes/0/channels/0/wave.Description: Contains the acquired Scope measurement data.

scopes/0/channels/1/enable.Description: Enables recording for this Scope channel.

scopes/0/channels/1/wave.Description: Contains the acquired Scope measurement data.

scopes/0/channels/2/enable.Description: Enables recording for this Scope channel.

scopes/0/channels/3/enable.Description: Enables recording for this Scope channel.

scopes/0/channels/3/wave.Description: Contains the acquired Scope measurement data.

scopes/0/enable.Description: Enables the acquisition of Scope shots. Goes back to 0 (disabled) after the scope shot has been acquired.

scopes/0/length.Description: Defines the length of the recorded Scope shot in number of samples.

scopes/0/segments/count.Description: Specifies the number of segments to be recorded in device memory. The maximum Scope shot size is given by the available memory divided by the number of segments.

scopes/0/segments/enable.Description: Enable segmented Scope recording. This allows for full bandwidth recording of Scope shots with a minimum dead time between individual shots.

scopes/0/single.Description: Puts the Scope into single shot mode.

scopes/0/time.Description: Defines the time base of the Scope.

scopes/0/trigger/delay.Description: The delay of a Scope measurement. A negative delay results in data being acquired before the trigger point. The resolution is 2 ns.

scopes/0/trigger/enable.Description: When triggering is enabled scope data are acquired every time the defined trigger condition is met.

Options.1: "on": ON: Trigger based scope shot acquisition

stats/cmdstream/bytesreceived.Description: Number of bytes received on the command stream from the device since session start.

stats/cmdstream/bytessent.Description: Number of bytes sent on the command stream from the device since session start.

stats/cmdstream/packetslost.Description: Number of command packets lost since device start. Command packets contain device settings that are sent to and received from the device.

stats/cmdstream/packetsreceived.Description: Number of packets received on the command stream from the device since session start.

stats/cmdstream/packetssent.Description: Number of packets sent on the command stream to the device since session start.

stats/cmdstream/pending.Description: Number of buffers ready for receiving command packets from the device.

stats/cmdstream/processing.Description: Number of buffers being processed for command packets. Small values indicate proper performance. For a TCP/IP interface, command packets are sent using the TCP protocol.

stats/datastream/bandwidth.Description: Data streaming bandwidth usage on the physical network connection between device and data server.

stats/datastream/bytesreceived.Description: Number of bytes received on the data stream from the device since session start.

stats/datastream/packetslost.Description: Number of data packets lost since device start. Data packets contain measurement data.

stats/datastream/packetsreceived.Description: Number of packets received on the data stream from the device since session start.

stats/datastream/pending.Description: Number of buffers ready for receiving data packets from the device.

stats/datastream/processing.Description: Number of buffers being processed for data packets. Small values indicate proper performance. For a TCP/IP interface, data packets are sent using the UDP protocol.

system/activeinterface.Description: Currently active interface of the device.

system/boardrevisions/0.Description: Hardware revision of the motherboard containing the FPGA.

system/boardrevisions/1.Description: Hardware revision of the Signal Output board.

system/clocks/referenceclock/in/freq.Description: Indicates the frequency of the reference clock.

system/clocks/referenceclock/in/source.Description: The intended reference clock source. When the source is changed, all the instruments connected with ZSync links will be disconnected. The connection should be re-established manually.

Options.0: "internal": The internal clock is intended to be used as the frequency and time base reference.
Options.1: "external": An external clock is intended to be used as the frequency and time base reference. Provide a clean and stable 10 MHz or 100 MHz reference to the appropriate back panel connector.
Options.2: "zsync": The ZSync clock is intended to be used as the frequency and time base reference.

Options.0: "internal": The internal clock is used as the frequency and time base reference.
Options.1: "external": An external clock is used as the frequency and time base reference.
Options.2: "zsync": The ZSync clock is used as the frequency and time base reference.

Options.0: Reference clock has been locked on.
Options.1: There was an error locking onto the reference clock signal.
Options.2: The device is busy trying to lock onto the reference clock signal.

system/clocks/referenceclock/out/enable.Description: Enable clock signal on the reference clock output. When the clock output is turned on or off, all the instruments connected with ZSync links will be disconnected. The connection should be re-established manually.

system/clocks/referenceclock/out/freq.Description: Select the frequency of the output reference clock. Only 10 MHz and 100 MHz are allowed. When the frequency is changed, all the instruments connected with ZSync links will be disconnected. The connection should be re-established manually.

system/fwlog.Description: Returns log output of the firmware.

system/fwlogenable.Description: Enables logging to the fwlog node.

system/fwrevision.Description: Revision of the device-internal controller software.

system/identify.Description: Setting this node to 1 will cause all frontpanel LEDs to blink for 5 seconds, then return to their previous state.

system/interfacespeed.Description: Speed of the currently active interface (USB only).

system/nics/0/defaultgateway.Description: Default gateway configuration for the network connection.

system/nics/0/defaultip4.Description: IPv4 address of the device to use if static IP is enabled.

system/nics/0/defaultmask.Description: IPv4 mask in case of static IP.

system/nics/0/mac.Description: Current MAC address of the device network interface.

system/nics/0/saveip.Description: If written, this action will program the defined static IP address to the device.

system/nics/0/static.Description: Enable this flag if the device is used in a network with fixed IP assignment without a DHCP server.

system/owner.Description: Returns the current owner of the device (IP).

system/properties/freqresolution.Description: The number of bits used to represent a frequency.

system/properties/freqscaling.Description: The scale factor to use to convert a frequency represented as a freqresolution-bit integer to a floating point value.

system/properties/maxfreq.Description: The maximum oscillator frequency that can be set.

system/properties/maxtimeconstant.Description: The maximum demodulator time constant that can be set.

system/properties/minfreq.Description: The minimum oscillator frequency that can be set.

system/properties/mintimeconstant.Description: The minimum demodulator time constant that can be set.

system/properties/negativefreq.Description: Indicates whether negative frequencies are supported.

system/properties/timebase.Description: Minimal time difference between two timestamps. The value is equal to 1/(maximum sampling rate).

system/shutdown.Description: Sending a '1' to this node initiates a shutdown of the operating system on the device. It is recommended to trigger this shutdown before switching the device off with the hardware switch at the back side of the device.

system/stall.Description: Indicates if the network connection is stalled.

system/swtriggers/0/single.Description: Issues a single software trigger event.

system/update.Description: Requests update of the device firmware and bitstream from the dataserver.
